This was difficult to prepare. I was so lucky to have a Kitchen Aid special attachment and a culinary degree to assist me in this endeavor. The recipe is all off in regards to the broth amount necessary. I will admit the soup did turn out delicious, but a lot of work for your average cook! Roasting the vegetables is the way to go and adding a little cream in the actual soup as well as whipping and dolloping on top for the end presentation. I used ground cloves (not whole) and a bit of ground nutmeg on the vegetables while they were roasting. Good, but would only make for a special occasion.

